<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74bdcdea-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102"><num value="230102">§ 230102.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of the corporation are fraternal, patriotic, historical, charitable, and educational, and are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdeb-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to preserve and strengthen comradeship among its members;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdec-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to assist worthy comrades;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcded-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to perpetuate the memory and history of our dead, and to assist their surviving spouses and orphans;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdee-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> to maintain true allegiance to the Government of the United States, and fidelity to its Constitution and laws;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdef-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> to foster true patriotism;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdf0-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> to maintain and extend the institutions of American freedom; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74bdcdf1-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s230102/7"><num value="7">(7)</num><content> to preserve and defend the United States from all enemies.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id74bdcdf2-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1481">112 Stat. 1481</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/107/242/s2">Pub. L. 107–242, § 2</ref>, <date date="2002-10-16">Oct. 16, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1497">116 Stat. 1497</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/199/s1/b">Pub. L. 113–199, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-04">Dec. 4, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2058">128 Stat. 2058</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
